  "changes": {
    "oija": {
      "id": "oija",
      "title": "Add output feedback to opencode run command",
      "body": "\n## Goal\nAdd output feedback to the 'pebbles start' command so users know when opencode is working.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [x] Add --print-logs flag to pebbles start command\n- [x] --print-logs flag passes through to opencode run command\n- [x] On non-Unix systems, stdout/stderr is inherited when --print-logs is set\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nAdded a new --print-logs flag to the 'pebbles start' command:\n\n### Changes Made:\n1. **src/cli.rs:52-54** - Added --print-logs flag to Start command with help text\n2. **src/main.rs:27,34** - Updated Start command handler to pass print_logs parameter\n3. **src/commands/start.rs:13,78-80,84,89-101** - \n   - Updated function signature to accept print_logs parameter\n   - Pass --print-logs to opencode when flag is set\n   - On non-Unix systems, inherit stdout/stderr when flag is set\n\n### Usage:\n```\npebbles start <id> --print-logs\n```\n\nThis will show opencode's output/logs to the console instead of running silently.\n\n## Log\n- 2026-02-19: Added --print-logs flag to pebbles start command\n",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "high",
      "changelog_type": null,
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:49:43.672257Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-19T13:35:13.125266Z"
    },
    "hoy9": {
      "id": "hoy9",
      "title": "Add support for issues with dependencies",
      "body": "Docket would call these epics, not the world's biggest fan of epic, but we want to track the idea of dependencies between issues and also show that in the list view. This means the list view is going to need a tree mode. so the \"list\" view should probably not draw boxes around everything - the table code should not have borders but still help us control the output (i.e. the width.)",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "changelog_type": null,
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:37:31.482437Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-19T15:34:57.901739Z"
    },
    "lx24": {
      "id": "lx24",
      "title": "id prefix doesn't include complete items",
      "body": "\n## Log\n- 2026-02-19: Fixed ID prefix highlighting to include completed items\n\n## Implementation\n- Modified `calculate_unique_prefixes` in `src/commands/list.rs` to use all changes from the database when computing unique prefixes\n- This ensures the list view shows the correct minimum unique prefix even when completed items are hidden\n- Fixed pre-existing test compilation issues (using `ID` instead of `Id`)\n- Fixed pre-existing clippy warnings in other files\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [x] ID prefix calculation in list view includes completed items\n- [x] The unique prefix shown in the UI correctly reflects the minimum needed to disambiguate from all changes\n- [x] All tests pass\n- [x] Code compiles without warnings",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "changelog_type": null,
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-19T14:39:16.189076Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-19T15:19:42.275819Z"
    },
    "0zu0": {
      "id": "0zu0",
      "title": "add plan command",
      "body": "## Goal\nImplement a `plan` command for pebbles that helps users break down and enrich existing issues by invoking opencode's /plan command.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] Command opens and reads the issue\n- [x] Displays change details before invoking opencode\n- [x] Invokes `opencode run /plan` for the user\n- [x] Works with optional ID or current workspace\n- [x] Creates `.opencode/commands/plan.md` prompt\n\n## Context\n\nThe plan command should:\n1. Display the change details\n2. Launch opencode with `opencode run /plan`\n3. Set PEBBLES_CHANGE and PEBBLES_VCS environment variables\n4. The plan.md prompt guides the LLM through:\n   - Reviewing acceptance criteria\n   - Scanning the codebase for context\n   - Creating an implementation checklist\n   - Identifying dependencies\n   - Updating the change body\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nCreated:\n- `src/commands/plan.rs` - Displays change and launches opencode\n- `.opencode/commands/plan.md` - LLM prompt for planning workflow\n\nLog:\n- 2026-02-19: Implemented plan command that invokes opencode run /plan\n- 2026-02-19: Created plan.md with structured planning workflow",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "changelog_type": "feature",
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T22:40:38.651291Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-19T15:47:27.159288Z"
    },
    "2p4t": {
      "id": "2p4t",
      "title": "abc",
      "body": "\n## Implementation Notes\n\nImplemented unique prefix highlighting for change IDs in the 'pebbles show' command.\n\n### Changes Made:\n1. Added 'unique_prefix_len()' function in src/commands/mod.rs:74 to calculate the minimum prefix length needed to uniquely identify a change ID among all others\n2. Added 'format_id_with_unique_prefix()' function in src/commands/mod.rs:96 to format the ID with the unique prefix in bold cyan and the rest dimmed\n3. Updated 'show' command in src/commands/show.rs:20-26 to use the new formatting\n\n### Technical Details:\n- The unique prefix is calculated by comparing the target ID against all other change IDs\n- The shortest prefix that makes the ID unique is highlighted\n- Format: unique prefix in bold cyan, remaining characters dimmed\n- Example: If change '2p4t' is the only one starting with '2', it will display as **2**p4t (with '2' bold and 'p4t' dimmed)\n\n## Log\n- 2026-02-18: Implemented unique prefix highlighting for change IDs\n",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
      "changelog_type": null,
      "parent": null,
      "children": [],
      "dependencies": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-02-18T21:06:10.592887Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-02-18T21:14:31.428830Z"
    },
    "fq24": {
      "id": "fq24",
      "title": "abcd",
      "body": "We need a CLI command that lets us edit the title of an issue.\n\n## Implementation\n\nThe functionality already exists via the `pebbles update` command:\n\n```\npebbles update <id> --title \"new title\"\n```\n\n## Log\n- 2026-02-18: Verified `pebbles update --title` already provides this functionality\n- 2026-02-18: Fixed pre-existing clippy warnings across the codebase",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": "medium",
